{
  "stem": "24163.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And some didn't make it, but I was saved.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I did not-- I did not have to go to the Battle of the Bulge.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was south of it at a town near Vichy, near [NON-ENGLISH], which is all in Alsace-Lorraine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's where my unit was based.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, shortly after the Battle of the Ardennes was over and done with, we had to then pack up our unit and follow combat units into Germany.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went-- we criss-crossed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We went into Germany.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we actually went back into France.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The border was sort of a zigzag.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And some parts had been liberated, others had not.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So one day I was in Germany, and another time I went back for the second time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I have a letter which talks of an experience in one German town that we had liberated where I was then assigned to requisition housing for all our unit that no longer wanted to live in tents.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, we were in tents-- either pup tents or regular tents-- all across France.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "All across France, we were in these units, in these pup tents or regular tents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when we got to Germany and they found out I spoke German, I quickly requisitioned houses, first for the officers-- naturally, I always saw to it that I have good quarters for myself-- and for the troops.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And some-- one of these experience, I have in a letter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And if you don't mind, I'll read excerpts.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A letter which I wrote to my wife on the 26th of March, 1945.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I write here that 'We've been moving around quite a bit lately.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm now deep in Germany--' it wasn't that deep, but deep for us-- '--and quite a stretch from France's border.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
